message.content:
cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.AR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the performance evaluation of satellite and terrestrial cellular networks in terms of different KPIs. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the Modulation Coding Scheme (MCS) index, which is related to information theory. 
- cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) is another possible category as the paper deals with the comparison of different backhauling nodes and their impact on mobile networks. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses a real satellite backhaul deployment and works in Ka band, which involves hardware components. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the existence of a trade-off between the supported number of users on satellite link and the GTP-U acceleration rate, which can be seen as a control problem.
